==English==
[[Category:English eponyms]]
===Etymology===
Named after the [[w:William Archibald Spooner|Reverend W. A. Spooner]] (1844-1930), who is supposed to have habitually made such slip-ups.

===Pronunciation===
*spo͞onʹərĭzəm, /<tt>"spu:n@rIz@m</tt>/
*{{IPA|/ˈspuːnərɪzəm/}}
